## Why AGPL-3.0?

MashupForge is open source. The core is licensed under AGPL-3.0 to
ensure that improvements to the open-source project are shared back with
the community, including when the software is run as a network service.

The AGPL-3.0 license is the standard choice for open-source projects
with a planned hosted / SaaS offering, and is used by projects such as
Plausible Analytics, Bitwarden, Nextcloud, Mattermost, MinIO, Directus,
and Mastodon.

## What this means in practice

- You can use, modify, and redistribute MashupForge freely.
- If you run a modified version as a network service, you must publish
  your modifications under the same license.
- A separate, proprietary SaaS / hosted offering that talks to the
  open-source core via a network API is permitted (this is the standard
  open-core pattern; see AGPL §5 and §13 for the network use clause).

See https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html for a human-readable
explanation, or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.txt for the full
legal text.
